data.description: HIGHEST & BEST OFFER is due by 12pm Monday 4/29/2024. DECISION WILL BE MADE the same day by 3:15pm on Monday, 4/29/2024. Welcome to 7423 160th Place, Tinley Park! This SHARP raised ranch has the LARGEST DECK in town! STRIKING EXTERIOR: Gray siding, earthy brick hues, a black roof, and a fashionable red door set against lush green grass give this home a DISTINCTIVE APPEARANCE!    The MAIN FLOOR features an open concept with a spacious, sunny living room, formal dining room, and a great kitchen. There are three bedrooms and a full bathroom. Walk out from the dining room onto the LARGEST DECK IN TOWN, big enough to accommodate a bar-height table, a cozy sitting area with a little firepit, grill and a dining table for six people. When the tree by the deck is in full bloom - deck becomes very private. The sellers love their deck so much that they contemplated detaching it from the house and taking it with them, as they practically live on it year-round. After 3 days of their realtor's determined persuasion - sellers finally agreed to leave the deck attached to the home for future owners.  The WALK-OUT BASEMENT could very well be what many are looking for in a home - an in-law arrangement. The FINISHED BASEMENT offers ample space to create a fourth bedroom, and a full bathroom and family room are already in place. The current owners have arranged the basement so they never had to leave the house for entertainment - they've installed a fun bar that leads straight out to the backyard, where a delightful firepit area awaits for watching fireworks and simply hanging out. The fenced yard provides plenty of space for playing games or gardening, or both. You'll be pleasantly surprised by the 3 garden beds and what they might yield in the summer. Is this your home?
